## Project Deployment

Run the following shell commands to deploy the project:

```shell
dr task run infra:up-yes
```

In case the deployment process fails, you can try deleting it by running the following command:

```shell
dr task run infra:down-yes
```

## Local Development

One-time setup (deploys backing infrastructure and prints OTel credentials):

```shell
dr start
```

Re-print OTel credentials without re-deploying:

```shell
dr task run infra:local-experimentation-otel-setup
```

## Local Tracing (OTel)

OTel write header must use `experiment_container-<use-case-id>`, **not** `use_case-<id>`.
The DR authorization API stores use cases internally as `experiment_container`; `use_case` is the user-facing alias accepted only by the read APIs.

Local dashboard: `dr experimentation --entity-type experiment_container --entity-id <id>` → http://127.0.0.1:8090 (runs in foreground, Ctrl+C to stop)

```shell
task infra:tracing:start   # start local OTel dashboard
task infra:tracing:stop    # stop local OTel dashboard
```

See [docs/base/local-tracing.md](../docs/base/local-tracing.md) for full setup.
